15:41.566 --> 15:43.442
Uh-oh.
What happened, E?

15:43.526 --> 15:45.736
Haggis trying to cast you
as a pygmy drug mule?

15:45.820 --> 15:49.031
- Vince wants off "Aquaman. "
- What is this, deja vu all over again?

15:49.115 --> 15:51.450
- What did Haggis say?
- He said he needs all 90 days.

15:51.534 --> 15:55.162
Noah can build an ark and save
all of God's creatures in 40 days.

15:55.246 --> 15:57.372
He can't shoot a movie in 65?

15:57.457 --> 15:59.916
- Is there anything you can do?
- I can't control Haggis.

16:00.001 --> 16:02.377
Well what if we call Cameron?
I can't even believe he's ready

16:02.462 --> 16:04.046
to do "A2" so soon.

16:05.673 --> 16:07.799
He's not signed on to do "A2."

16:08.217 --> 16:10.677
- What?
- He just signed on to do the first one.

16:10.762 --> 16:12.471
Then why is Vince
signed on for three?

16:12.555 --> 16:13.972
That's the way it works
with actors.

16:14.057 --> 16:15.307
Cameron was the only
reason I did the movie

16:15.391 --> 16:16.892
in the first place.
Who's directing?

16:19.020 --> 16:20.729
- Michael Bay.
- Jesus Christ!

16:20.813 --> 16:23.482
- They're just rushing this thing out.
- Listen, Vinnie.

16:23.566 --> 16:26.818
This is what studios do.
The thing is a monster hit.

16:26.903 --> 16:28.904
They're just trying to take
advantage of it, that's all.

16:28.988 --> 16:30.822
- I haven't even seen a script.
- They're working on it.

16:30.907 --> 16:33.283
- Andrew Kevin Walker writing?
- Kevin Smith.

16:33.826 --> 16:36.745
- Oh boy.
- Fuck you, Ari. I want off this movie.

16:36.829 --> 16:38.413
We'll go to Warner's,
we'll ask them for more days.

16:38.498 --> 16:41.249
There are no more days. What are
you talking about? You were there.

16:41.334 --> 16:43.835
Alan was nice enough to give us 65.
He didn't even have to do that.

16:43.920 --> 16:46.338
- I'm not doing this movie.
- Vince, you signed a contract.

16:46.422 --> 16:48.548
And I know that you
are a man of your word.

16:48.633 --> 16:51.385
Oh yeah, and are you?
Are you a man of your word, Ari?

16:51.469 --> 16:54.054
- I never lied to you.
- You told me if I did "Aquaman,"

16:54.138 --> 16:56.181
- that I could get "Medellin. "
- You got "Medellin. " I can't help

16:56.265 --> 17:00.102
the timing. Listen, I would if I could.
Remember, I don't get paid shit on this.

17:00.186 --> 17:02.020
It all goes
to my former employer.

17:02.105 --> 17:04.356
Look, Vinnie, I know that
you would kill that role.

17:04.440 --> 17:07.108
I know the timing sucks.
But be a man.

17:15.702 --> 17:17.911
I'll call Haggis,
tell him I'm off the movie.

17:18.162 --> 17:19.663
I'm sorry, Vinnie.

17:29.716 --> 17:32.217
- Just running this shit all day, huh?
All day.

17:32.301 --> 17:34.761
This keeps up, you'll have to get
your own channel on Sirius.

17:34.846 --> 17:36.513
Yeah, I got to say, Turtle,

17:36.597 --> 17:39.266
took you longer than you promised, man,
but you came through.

17:39.350 --> 17:41.143
You ain't seen nothing yet.

17:41.477 --> 17:43.311
Hey, yo, Keshawn,
let me get the box, man.

17:47.734 --> 17:50.277
- Yo, you got me a gift?
- Just a little something.

17:50.361 --> 17:52.946
Sai, don't go spending all
your money just yet, man.

17:54.115 --> 17:57.159
- Try it on.
- Yo, I can't accept this.

17:57.702 --> 17:59.911
No, don't worry. They're CZs
but I plan on replacing them

17:59.996 --> 18:01.496
as soon as I can afford it.

18:04.333 --> 18:05.792
That's tight, man.
Thank you.

18:09.839 --> 18:13.258
- Oh, hey, Paul.
- Hey. I couldn't sleep.

18:13.468 --> 18:16.511
I just keep trying to picture this movie
without Vince and I can't do it.

18:17.054 --> 18:18.847
Well, what can we do?

18:19.182 --> 18:20.474
Brainstorm.

18:31.944 --> 18:34.362
I got nothing.
Nothing.

18:34.906 --> 18:36.448
- Nothing.
- Nothing.

18:36.532 --> 18:37.532
Nothing.

18:37.742 --> 18:40.660
You ever consider cutting out
all the flashbacks, Paul?

18:42.455 --> 18:44.164
- No.
Now this may be retarded,

18:44.248 --> 18:45.707
or maybe I'm just baked,

18:46.501 --> 18:49.044
but you said you wanted Vince
to gain 50 Ibs. For the part, right?

18:49.128 --> 18:51.671
70. It's more authentic.

18:51.756 --> 18:53.882
Right, but you still need him
skinny for the early years.

18:54.258 --> 18:56.843
- Yeah.
- So you shoot the first half now

18:56.928 --> 18:58.929
before "Aquaman 2"
while he's skinny.

18:59.055 --> 19:02.307
Shoot the second half after he wraps
when Vince piles on the pasta.

19:02.391 --> 19:04.976
Like De Niro in "Raging Bull. "
- Like Clooney in "Syriana. "

19:05.061 --> 19:07.354
Or Johnny Chase
in "The Commish"

19:07.563 --> 19:09.731
when I played
that bulimic pedophile.

19:10.149 --> 19:12.776
- Did you see that one, Paul?
- No.

19:13.444 --> 19:15.153
But you know what?

19:15.238 --> 19:16.780
- This could work.
- You think?

19:16.864 --> 19:19.157
- This could fucking work, man.
- Definitely.

19:19.242 --> 19:20.700
Fuckin' A!

19:20.785 --> 19:22.118
Good work, E.

19:22.203 --> 19:24.704
Yeah well, somebody's got to
make shit happen when you can't.

19:24.789 --> 19:27.082
Save one pat on your back
for me. Huh, buddy?

19:27.166 --> 19:28.834
Yeah yeah yeah.
Look, you've got to call Alan.

19:28.918 --> 19:30.961
Tell him Vince wants to take him
out to dinner to say thanks.

19:31.045 --> 19:33.171
Wow, our boy is really
becoming a man now, huh?

19:33.256 --> 19:34.714
I'll talk to you later, Ari.

19:35.550 --> 19:37.759
Call Alan at Warner.
Set up a dinner for four, please.

19:37.844 --> 19:40.345
- Today is going to be a big day.
- For you maybe.

19:40.721 --> 19:42.889
Some guy at Atlantic Records
keeps calling me every 10 minutes.

19:42.974 --> 19:44.266
- What does he want?
- I have no idea.

19:44.350 --> 19:46.351
He just keeps saying
something about Saigon.

19:46.435 --> 19:48.061
Saigon?
That's interesting.

19:48.145 --> 19:50.021
- Get him on the phone right now.
- Right now? Okay.

19:56.571 --> 19:59.197
Oh, in the hole!
Just like Tiger at Sawgrass.

19:59.282 --> 20:01.241
Yeah, more like my six-year-old niece
at Nunley's.

20:01.325 --> 20:04.578
Are you kidding?
Atlantic Records called you?

20:04.662 --> 20:07.163
- ARl: Sony and Interscope too.
- Holy shit!

20:07.248 --> 20:10.542
Anyway, tell Vince and E
8:00 at The Palms with Alan.

20:10.626 --> 20:12.752
8:00 at The Palm with Alan.
What else, Ari?

20:12.837 --> 20:14.963
Just make sure
they're on time, Turtle. I got to go.

20:15.298 --> 20:16.715
- Wait, Ari.
- Yeah, Turtle?

20:16.799 --> 20:18.758
- Are you fucking with me?
- A little bit.

20:18.843 --> 20:20.719
- This is sick, right?
- It is sick.

20:20.803 --> 20:23.388
As soon as we settle this stuff with
Vince I'm gonna set up some meetings.

20:23.472 --> 20:26.683
- Your boy's gonna get a deal.
- Holy shit.

20:26.767 --> 20:29.644
I think your life's
about to change, Turtle.

20:33.274 --> 20:34.399
What happened?

20:34.483 --> 20:36.276
Saigon is gonna get a deal!

20:36.569 --> 20:38.403
Ari just said my life
was gonna change.

20:38.487 --> 20:40.447
- Awesome.
- Come on. Congratulations, buddy.

20:40.531 --> 20:42.407
- Thank you, E.
- Good work.

20:42.491 --> 20:45.869
Vince, thank you so much.
That Big Boy thing put me over the top.

20:45.953 --> 20:49.205
Hey, I'm happy for you, bro.
I'm happy for you.

21:02.929 --> 21:04.679
Come to Daddy, sweetie.

21:08.517 --> 21:09.809
She still mad at me?

21:09.894 --> 21:11.937
- No, she's mad at Max now.
- What did he do?

21:12.021 --> 21:13.855
Took a movie
in Kazakhstan.

21:15.191 --> 21:17.734
I'm so glad our daughter's
tears make you so happy.

21:17.818 --> 21:19.945
Baby, those tears
mean our little girl's

21:20.029 --> 21:22.530
gonna stay our little girl
for at least another day.

21:24.700 --> 21:25.867
Ari...

21:25.952 --> 21:28.536
Now how about a quick blowjob
before my Vince dinner?

21:29.538 --> 21:31.247
What?

21:33.292 --> 21:35.377
Order whatever you want,
Drama, it's on me.

21:35.586 --> 21:37.128
I don't need you to pay
for shit of mine, Turtle.

21:37.213 --> 21:40.465
With Ari on my side my life's
about to change also.

21:41.884 --> 21:44.260
You know, we had "Medellin"
first over at my studio.

21:44.387 --> 21:46.054
- Really?
- Sure, yeah.

21:46.138 --> 21:47.889
- Let it go.
- Why?

21:48.265 --> 21:50.558
